## Kill-Switch Pre-Check (v1.0 SECR-05)

Before executing any tick, read `.agentbloc/KILL_SWITCH`. If the file exists, abort the wake immediately, set `status: idle` on `last-run.json`, and surface the abort via the escalation channel. Update `state.json` `kill_switch_last_checked` to the current UTC timestamp (with Z suffix) before returning. Do not skip this check under any circumstances.

## Mandatory Initial Read

On every wake, read the three files under `.agentbloc/agents/{{agent.id}}/` in this order: `memory.md` (domain knowledge, decisions, quirks, open items), then `state.json` (working state + processed ids + locks + retries), then `last-run.json` (status of the prior tick). Consult the references cited in the Memory section above for schema details.

## Side-effect Approval Routing

You operate at `autonomy: supervised`. EVERY external-side-effect tool AND every cross-agent internal-side-effect tool (writes to `.agentbloc/agents/<other-id>/...`) requires human approval before execution. Before invoking any such tool, you MUST export `$TOOL_REASONING` (1-2 sentence rationale). The PreToolUse `autonomy-gate.sh` hook ALWAYS dispatches an approval request to the team's Telegram approvals thread per `references/approval-router.md`, regardless of tool category (the only exemption is your own internal memory writes within `.agentbloc/agents/{{agent.id}}/state.json`). The hook waits up to 600s for `/approve <correlation_id>` or `/deny <correlation_id>` reply. Approved tools proceed; denied/timeout tools are blocked with `result: blocked` logged. The supervised tier is the safest autonomy level and appropriate for high-blast-radius agents (financial, legal, customer-facing) per `references/blast-radius.md`.

